The paper deals with domain adaptation, which is a common problem in machine learning and computer vision. The paper proposes a deep learning framework for unsupervised domain adaptation that leverages task-specific information to improve the alignment between the source and target domains. This makes it likely that the paper belongs to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), or neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
